(LC 12)
2/24/26 (RLM/ps)
Requested by Representative WRIGHT
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4075
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, line 2, after “finance” delete the rest of the
2 line and line 3 and insert “; and declaring an emergency.”.
3 Delete lines 5 through 28 and delete pages 2 and 3 and insert:
4 “SECTION 1. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part
5 of ORS chapter 285A.
6 “SECTION 2. (1) On or before April 1, 2027, the State Treasurer shall
7 guarantee an eligible rural hospital stabilization loan under this sec-
8 tion.
9 “(2) A rural hospital stabilization loan that is eligible to be guar-
10 anteed under this section must:
11 “(a) Be made to a hospital that:
12 “(A) Is governed by a publicly elected board; and
13 “(B) Receives Medicare reimbursement on the basis of diagnostic
14 related groups;
15 “(b) Be used only to address cash shortages or to refinance existing
16 debt and not to expand services, facilities or operations or to make
17 capital improvements;
18 “(c) Have a maturity date of no later than 20 years after the closing
19 date of the loan;
20 “(d) Be a fully amortized loan with no provisions allowing or re-
21 quiring interest-only or balloon payments;

1 “(e) Be made by a single lender or loan syndicate;
2 “(f) Be secured by a first position lien on substantially all of the
3 hospital’s real property and material equipment;
4 “(g) Provide the State of Oregon with all rights typical of a secured
5 party in a commercial transaction;
6 “(h) Require the hospital and lender to exercise all commercially
7 reasonable efforts, not including foreclosure upon the hospital’s real
8 property or equipment securing the loan, to meet the debt obligation
9 before pursuing the guarantee;
10 “(i) Be provided to the State Treasurer; and
11 “(j) Require the hospital or lender to give prompt notice to the
12 State Treasurer:
13 “(A) When the loan is paid in full;
14 “(B) If servicing of the loan is transferred;
15 “(C) If the loan is in default; or
16 “(D) If the hospital executes additional loan agreements or modifi-
17 cations to the loan guaranteed under this section.
18 “(3) The guarantee of a loan under this section terminates upon the
19 earliest of:
20 “(a) Thirty days following the loan’s maturity date;
21 “(b) Replacement of the loan guaranteed under this section with a
22 new loan to the hospital; or
23 “(c) Full repayment of the loan to the guaranteed lender.
24 “(4) A hospital whose loan is guaranteed under this section shall
25 provide annual reports to the State Treasurer indicating:
26 “(a) The outstanding loan balance;
27 “(b) The repayment status of the loan; and
28 “(c) The financial standing of the hospital.
29 “(5) A guarantee issued under this section may only be payable
30 from moneys in the Unclaimed Property and Estates Fund established
HB 4075-8 2/24/26
Proposed Amendments to HB 4075 Page 2

1 under ORS 98.389 and does not constitute a debt or obligation of the
2 State of Oregon.
3 “SECTION 3. Section 4 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part
4 of ORS 98.302 to 98.436.
5 “SECTION 4. Notwithstanding ORS 98.389 (3), the State Treasurer
6 shall expend up to $44 million of the moneys in the Unclaimed Prop-
7 erty and Estates Fund established under ORS 98.389 as needed to fulfill
8 contractual obligations on a guarantee issued under section 2 of this
9 2026 Act.
10 “SECTION 5. Section 4 of this 2026 Act is repealed on January 2,
11 2048.
12 “SECTION 6. Section 4 of this 2026 Act does not become operative
13 until and unless, on or before April 1, 2027, a loan is guaranteed under
14 section 2 of this 2026 Act.
15 “SECTION 7. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate
16 preservation of the public peace, health and safety, an emergency is
17 declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect on its passage.”.
